headline: Kevin Warsh becoming new frontrunner to be Trump's Fed nominee
summary: President Trump said on Friday that it appears unlikely that he will pick Kevin Hassett to be his nominee for the next chair of the Federal Reserve, according to reporting from Bloomberg: "I would lose you. It's a serious concern to me." Kevin Hassett — who was initially thought to be the frontrunner for the position — currently serves in the Trump administration as the director of the National Economic Council. Yahoo Finance Senior Fed Reporter Jennifer Schonberger outlines how former Fed governor Kevin Warsh is becoming the new favorite to be Trump's nominee, while also discussing the latest economic commentary from the Fed's Vice Chair for Supervision Michelle Bowman. Be sure to check out Jennifer Schonberger's profiles on each of the possible candidates to be the next Fed chair: Kevin Hassett, former Fed Governor Kevin Warsh, Fed Governor Chris Waller, Fed Vice Chair of Supervision Michelle Bowman, and BlackRock's (BLK) head of fixed income Rick Rieder. Yahoo Finance interviewed Kevin Hassett in late November 2025. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.

headline: Trump may not pick Kevin Hassett to head Fed: 'I would lose you'

"I would lose you. It's a serious concern to me," Trump said, as reported by Bloomberg. Kevin Hassett currently serves in the Trump administration as the director of the National Economic Council.
